LINEECHO: Client line echo preference

Syntax: lineecho [on|off]

DESCRIPTION:
  Lineecho is primarily a MUD client feature, not a server command.
  Many clients (Mudlet, MUSHclient, etc.) can echo each command line
  locally before sending it to the game.

  This command stores an on/off flag on your character file in case
  a client reads it. The stock RiftsMUD server does not change how
  lines display based on this flag.

  Configure local line echo in your client preferences if typed lines
  do not appear in your output window.

SEE ALSO: triggers, prompt
